# Data Flow

> How a request travels from the edge through the layers and back.

## Typical request lifecycle

```
(request) → ui → runtime → service → repo → (storage)
                ↓         ↓         ↓
              Provider  Provider  Provider
              (auth)   (logging) (telemetry)
```

(Fill in: replace the diagram with the project's actual flow.)

## Failure modes

| Where | What can fail | Detection | Recovery |
|---|---|---|---|
| ui/ | malformed input | runtime type check | 400 response |
| service/ | business rule violation | unit test | 422 response |
| repo/ | storage unavailable | health check | retry + circuit breaker |

